inn1.comm: pitches it up and Watson drives firmly to mid-off, nice shot for nothing
back of a length, middle and leg, turned to square leg
leaves this one as it pitches outside off and shapes away nicely
comes onto the front foot and drives nicely to the man at cover
well thats a shocker, miles, miles down the leg side, just slipped out of Smith's hands and sprayed a month away from Ramdin, that is one of the biggest wides ever
just a wee bit short and Watson gets over it with a nice back cut
veers onto the pads and he clips it in the air over square leg
nice length but too fine and Paine shuffles across to glance, can't get bat on ball, but the little deflection off the pads evades a diving Ramdin
good length half a foot outside off, some shape, Paine leaves be
on a length outside off again, tempting a drive, but he says nope
short of a length and gets some lift to Paine, who stands up and allows the ball come on before angling the bat to pick up one to third man
shot man! Watson just sees the length on the shorter ball and in a flash pulls it high over midwicket and dumps it into the stands out there
fuller on middle and off and he leans into a drive to mid-on
on a length and he gets the wrists into play, turning the ball to leg
sees room on the wide half volley and reaches out, slashing an outer edge safely wide of the slips for four
goes back and pushes it to the off side, running hard
better ball, middle and leg, slanting in, pushed to midwicket
slants into Paine off a shorter length, he tries to nudge it but ends up mistiming the ball to the off side
short, comes on sharply, he tries to dab it fine but inside-edges
short of a length, Watson gets his back leg across and dabs the ball down to third man where Dowlin covers good distance and returns the ball
gets over the ball and steers it backward of point

look at that! There's only one slip now, and he's moved wide, and Watson edges the attempted swinging yorker outside off smack into the gaping hole between slip and Ramdin, had the man stayed where he was that could have been out
big shot down the ground this time, not timed well but he's sure of what he wants to do, Watson, planting his foot forward and driving the ball high over mid-off
goes for a heave across the line and gets hit in the midriff
short ball, Watson gets airborne while jumping back and defends to point
goes for the cut and gets cramped, resulting in an under edge past leg
fuller ball, he gets two-thirds forward and dabs it to cover
walks down the track, Smith holds back the length, Paine defends
shuffles across and turns the ball off the stumps to square leg
pitches it up outside off and he shoulders arms
good length, Watson strides forward and defends with soft hands, then picks up one quickly as the ball runs toward gully
drives a full ball but cannot beat the man at short cover
fuller and he drives straighter, back to the bowler
another meaty drive off the front foot but straight to mid-off this time
wider half-volley and he smashes it along the carpet to deep cover
driven back firmly to Smith, who fumbles the collection
walks across the sticks and intentionally flicks the ball over square

oh well held, Hinds! That's the catch of the summer! Watson leans forward to a length ball and goes downtown but miscues the shot, sending the ball miles up in the air, it looks like it will take some catching as Hinds runs back from mid-on, never taking his eyes off it, and then dives full stretch forward to clutch it as it dies on him, man oh man he had to cover a lot of ground and mind you he was running behind all the way, excellent effort from Hinds
pitches it up and he shoulders arms
back of a length and he defends
reaches out to a full ball and drives with a thick edge past gully
takes a movement forward, then back, and works the ball to square
another shuffle forward and back and then Paine slaps the wide ball past point, that was there to be hit and he duly put it away
up there on middle and off and he gets across to defend
just back of a length this time, Ponting makes sure off stump is covered before he defends to point
goes back to a shorter ball and forces it nicely past point
shuffles across and turns the ball off his hips to midwicket
fuller ball, some cut back in, punched nicely to cover
strays fine, Ponting gets across and deflects it to fine leg
gets back and cuts the short ball behind point for one
shapes back in off a length, he tries the flicks but gets a leading edge
on the walk, he punches a lovely drive past cover for three
fuller ball swings into the toes, he tries the flick and gets rapped
shorter in length, cut off the back foot but cant beat point
fuller outside off as he searches for swing, again Paine hangs on the back foot and this time slashes the ball to backward point
back of a length, Ponting gets in line and defends to point
goes back to the one slanting in, not really a short ball, and steers it wide of backward point
short of a length, some wobble off the seam, pushed to cover
goes back again and forces the ball past backward point
well done, Paine goes back and across and drops the ball near his feet, looks up at Ponting who harries down, Sammy tries to get across to field and gets tangled with Ponting but they get a single
ah, there's that Ponting lunge, losing a hand off the bat as he drives at moving delivery that clips the outer edge and flies into the gap between point and slip
banged in short, Ponting pulls past square out to the sweeper
full and wide, Paine reaches out and slashes it over backward point
pitched up again and he slashes, but point dives and intercepts
slices again to the off side for a single
full and Ponting slices over backward point, third man does the stopping
comes onto the front foot and pushes a drive to cover
pitches leg and straightens, Paine thinks about the on-drive but adjusts to play it back down the track
walks down the track and dabs the ball to midwicket
fuller ball, some swing, punched away to wide midwicket
lunges forward on the drive but inside-edges past leg stump
full ball, punched on the rise to mid-off, good shot that time
skips out to take on Sammy but can only drive the ball to extra cover
good start, on a length, some shape, Ponting pats it back
drags back the length, Ponting goes onto the back foot and punches the ball into the covers
goes back and slashes the ball in the air past gully
short and wide, there to be hit but Ponting gets an inside edge
likes the length of the offcutter and drives on the rise over mid-off, just hitting through the line and not bothering about keeping the ball down
even better! Pollard goes full and straight and Ponting does the same, punching the ball right back over his head for a flowing straight six, nice high elbow and all
gets over the bounce and dabs the ball to backward point
walks across and tickles the ball just wide of Ramdin
beaten this time, trying to cut one not short enough at all
dances out trying to hammer leather over cover but isn't near the wide ball and gets beaten
cuts back in off a length and Ponting pushes the ball to point
short of a length, he goes back and punches on the rise to cover
arm ball, Paine shuffles and turns it to midwicket
some turn, but again he shuffles and works it to midwicket
fuller ball slants back in, punched to the man at extra cover
walks down and flicks the full ball past square leg
tossed up, he gets a stride forward and drives it back
tossed up, again he gets forward and keeps it out
short of a length, he gets forward and taps it to cover, calls for the single, has to run hard to get down the other end too
opens the face to a wider ball and steers a single to third man
excellent catch at backward point, and its Pollard! A ripper, as they say, diving to his right to intercept a firm cut shot from Paine, he just leaped at it and the ball stuck
fuller ball slants in, White tries the on-drive and loses balance
pitched up, Ponting meets it with a solid defensive
pushes at the ball and runs it down to third man for one
quick through the air and defended towards silly point
lands outside off and he cuts down to sweeper cover
slower through the air and he defends towards cover and tells his partner to wait
pushed a full delivery down to mid-off
gets forward and defends
comes onto the front foot and pushes the ball to point, Ponting sets off, White stops and shoos his captain back as the fielder swoops in
straighter ball, tucked away past square leg
pitched up a foot outside off, White gets in and raises the bat
walks down, not to the pitch still so pats the ball back to Sammy
short ball, he tries to latch on and doesn't get a full hold, still manages to drag the ball down in front of midwicket
short of a length and defended
slower through the air and defended down the track
drives firmly to short cover
gets forward and drives to sweeper cover
opens the face and edges it to short third man
goes back and cuts to deep point
lunges forward and drives to cover, quiet over
gets forward and pushes him down to cover
tries to pinch the gap on the off side but finds point
squared up by a beauty outside the off stump, White wasn't sure whether to play or leave it
comes forward and gets a thick outside edge down to third man
gets beside the line and slices him down to deep point
slower in pace and he fetches it from outside off and pulls on one leg
comes down the pitch and drops the ball down to cover
gets on his knee and paddles him to down to fine leg

just over the rope and a valiant attempt by Pollard! Ponting chips down the track and lofts it down to long-on, the ball however dips and just clears the rope, Pollard throws himself backwards and tries to pull it off one-handed, reminded me of Vasbert Drakes' catch in the 2003 World Cup
makes room and cuts to deep point
gets forward and smothers the spin
gets forward and clips him to midwicket
gets forward and slices him to point
gets forward and drops the ball down to cover and sets off in a flash, excellent running and that's his fifty
just squeezes it past short cover for a single
angles towards the pads and he clips him down to midwicket
very good timing there, gives him width outside off and he rolls his wrists and slices it wide of point, didn't try to hit it too hard, nobody patrolling the rope there
shuffles and clips him to the leg side
gets forward and defends
gets forward and defends
gets forward and pushes him down to long-off
tossed up on leg and he clips him to the on side
quicker through the air and defended down the track
gets forward and drives to cover
gets down for a premediated paddle and places it to square leg
drops it on a good length and he punches it down to long-on
pushed to the pads and he clips it to short square leg
drops it towards cover and sets off for a quick single
down the leg side and wide called
slower off the pitch and tucked down to midwicket
gets on his knees and sweeps him firmly down to deep square
gets forward and defends
pushes it behind square on the off side
steps down the track to whack it through the off side but he slaps it past cover
clean hit! tossed up on middle stump and he gets down early enough and carts him high and far over deep midwicket
gets well forward and defends to the off side
punches it towards mid-on and sets off in a flash, the fielder takes aim at the bowler's end
gets forward and drives to mid-off
quicker through the air and knocked towards mid-on
clips it behind square on the on side
tossed up on middle and leg and pushed to mid-on
gets forward and smothers the spin
gets beside the line and chops him down to point
cuts back and he pushes it to the off side
good shot, fractionally short and he forces it down to deep midwicket, the ball is in the air for a while
fuller in length and clipped down to midwicket
gets a half stride forward and pushes it down the track
another well-controlled shot, the ball is pitched up on the pads and he whips it in the air down to deep midwicket, timing was the key
full on the pads and he pushes it down to long-on
on the pads and he clips it down to long-on
Pollard dives to his left and saves a few runs at least, good stop
Pollard in action at mid-on again, saves a single
opens the face and dabs him down to third man
gives him a lot of width outside off and he places it down to long-off
width again and he chops it down to point
effortless! Pitched up on the pads and a nonchalant swing of the bat is enough to comfortably clear mid-on

ouch! I don't think White saw that at all! It kicked up just a bit off a good length and he completely took his eyes off the ball as he shaped to evade it, the ball misses the grill and hits him on the side of the neck, he drops his bat in a flash and wanders away dazed, the physio comes out, and the good news is he's strapping his helmet back on
gets beside the line and steers him down to point
full on middle and leg and he drives him down to long-on
full on the pads and he works him down to long-on
clips the ball towards midwicket
no turn at all, he rocks back and punches it down to long-off
waits for the turn and cuts it late to short third man
flatter this time and pushed down to long-off
full on middle and pushed down the ground to long-on
short ball, sits up outside off, White stands up and pulls out to the sweeper in the deep
pitches this one up and White stabs at it
floats up the offcutter and White pummels a drive to mid-off
short of a length to Ponting who walks into the shot and pushes to midwicket
another short ball, White pulls to Deonarine at deep midwicket
goes back to steer this one to the man at backward point
tossed up and he pushes the ball to point
works this one to the leg side
well done, opens the face and guides the ball to third man
tossed up, Ponting drives it back
hangs in the air a bit longer, Ponting works it to midwicket
now White's turn to nudge the ball off his pads for a single
comes onto the front foot and dabs the ball square on the off
down the leg side, goes for the pull but the ball brushes his arm and slides down further, Ramdin does the diving
gets tall and punches the ball away
pitches and cuts in to White who waits before nudging it to cover
pitched up to Ponting who plays a flowing off-drive down the ground
too short and he gets down to paddle-pull it with the turn
better length, forcing him to come after it and push to cover
flighted into Ponting who uses his feet and flicks out to deep square
makes room and then drives inside-out in the air to long-off
swats this one to the leg side
goes back but has to adjust the stroke to defend the ball
hits a length and Ponting, committed to the front foot, checks the shot
walks across the stumps and nudges the ball toward midwicket
bangs in a short ball outside off which White tries to pull but takes it on the toe of the bat and the edge runs away
hits a good length and Ponting turns it from off to midwicket
there's the 200 up, as White goes back and cuts past point for two, it its also his fifty up in good time and after catching his breath he raises the bat
shorter ball, White allows it come on before dabbing to point
flat and short, White goes back and muscles it to midwicket
speared down the pads and Ponting glances it away
tossed up and he uses the wrists to turn the ball away
flatter ball, pushed away with ease for one more
whips it off the pads and gets one past square leg
tries the cut late cut and gets beaten, then curses in anger
pitches it up on the stumps, White pushes it past Rampaul
drags back the length and gets Ponting going back and across
floats up a cutter that brings Ponting a ways forward and defending
this time he meets the ball with a full face and drives to long-off
tries a big slog to one outside off but struggles for timing and Rampaul does the fielding
gets over the shorter ball and angles it down past backward point
goes for the slog sweep to one tossed up outside off but misses and leg byes are the signal
well bowled, gets some drift there and White has to defend
covers off stump this time and sweeps hard into the ground in front of square
presses forward and then hurries back to cut the ball past cover
dances out but Miller adjusts the length, so White defends to cover
uses his feet again and drives nicely past the man at cover
pitched up outside off, goes back and slices the ball past point
gets across and nudges the ball across the line to midwicket
goes back again and tucks it out to the deep
comes forward and then checks the shot to cover
again on the front foot and he pushes down to long-off
uses his feet and clips with the swing
turned away to the deep for one more
gets across and pulls out the paddle-sweep to fine leg
kneels down and sweeps hard to deep square leg
goes back and gets over the ball to cut out to deep cover
gone this time, trying another slog-sweep across the line but getting under it and giving Sammy at long-on an easy catch, and also Miller his first wicket on tour
tossed up on a length and Ponting presses it to cover
full on middle and leg, some swing, Voges turns it past square
slides on the pads and he clips him down to fine leg, the fielder gives the chase from short fine
tucks it straight to short fine and sets off and completes the single and completes the single to get to his hundred!
makes just a bit of room and scoops a pitched up delivery over extra cover bisects the gap
good length on the pads and he whips him down to midwicket
tucks it to midwicket and decides against the single
slower through the air and worked down to mid-on
comes over the wicket, he lunges forward and drives him down to cover
punches him down to mid-off and sets off
fuller on the pads and he tries to sweep it  and the ball just beats square leg, Miller looks disappointed
stays back and punches it down to cover
nice yorker on the pads and he just manages to whip it to the on side
take that! Pitched up on middle and leg and he bends his knee and slogs him, over wide long-on, effortless and that went rows back
drops it to the off side and he thinks of a single

tries to clear long-on but finds the fielder, Voges bends his knee slightly and scoops it high over the bowler's head, Miller cups it over his head and the momentum nearly takes him over the rope but he hangs on
shuffles and clips him down to square leg, Ponting darts out of his crease and scampers back
he moves across the stumps and tries to paddle it down to fine leg but he finds short fine leg, the ball is in the air and the ball dips and he takes it low falling forward
nice square drive, full and wide outside off and he bends full stretch and caresses it wide of backward point
full on the off stump and pushed down to the off side
terrible delivery down the leg side, Hussey tries to whip it away and the ball is so wide that it beats the keeper
low full toss outside the off stump and he squeezes it out to mid-off
on a length and he works it from off stump past midwicket
lunges forward and works the ball past the infield
pitches it up, Hopes works it to midwicket and sets off
comes forward and nudges the ball away
on leg stump and Hussey clips the ball down to fine leg
low full toss, not quite the yorker, which Hussey steers to third man
full on the off stump and he scoops it towards sweeper cover
chips down the track and mistimes the loft down to long-on, the fielder runs forward but the ball drops well short of him
aims for the yorker down the leg side and he shuffles slightly and gently tickles it wide of short fine leg
makes a bit of room and carves it over point, third man runs across and cuts it off
slower ball on the pads and he whips him away down to deep midwicket
that's a friendly full toss and he slams it away, aimed for the yorker, with an effortless swing he clears deep square leg
full on the pads and worked away to the on side
he makes room to a full delivery, gets under the bounce and scoops it over midwicket, good clean hit and very close to clearing the rope
makes room and jams out a yorker to cover point
backs away to a full delivery on the stumps and whips him away down to deep square leg
another clean hit, makes room and whips it flat and hard down to deep midwicket, Smith runs around quickly and cuts it off
crisp straight drive, Hussey gets behind the line to an attempted yorker and caresses it past the bowler
full on the pads and he clips it to the on side
tossed up on the pads and he tickles it to the on side
excellent shot! Tossed up on the off stump and he chips down the pitch and takes him downtown over extra cover, picks the gap there
tucks it down to fine leg and that's the fifty stand
plays the reverse sweep down to square leg
makes room and mistimes the drive back to the bowler
goes for the slog too early and the ball hits his arm and drops on the pitch

cleverly bowled actually, Pollard knew Hussey was targeting the leg side and didn't give him room to free his arms, he pitches it wide outside leg on seeing Hussey make room and advance down the pitch, the ball hits his body and deflects to the stumps
Johnson nearly gives his wicket away there, he tries to dab it down to third man almost feathers an edge
Johnson drops it on the pitch and sets off for a cheeky single, Pollard tries to kick the ball to the stumps but the batsman's home

terribly mixup there, Hopes slogs him down to deep midwicket, Smith runs forward for the catch, he can't get to it, the ball beats him and Dowlin runs from deep square leg, fails to watch the spin and overruns the ball
makes room and chops it to the off side
full on the pads and he works it down to deep midwicket
very cheeky and well done!  He picks the slower ball outside the off stump early, gets in position for the reverse sweep and paddles it hard past the wicketkeeper, agricultural shot
makes a bit of room and scoops him down to deep extra cover
pitched up outside the off stump and he makes room, gets under the bounce and scoops him flat to Smith and deep extra cover, he bends low and takes it
that will sting Sammy! Well directed yorker outside the off stump, Johnson swings and he gets an inside edge which just beats the stumps and the keeper
on the pads and he tries to shovel it down the leg side, goes to deep square leg

inn2.comm: short ball first up, which Gayle defends to the off side
good ball, short of a length and moving away, Gayle pulls the bat inside the line as the ball passes
much wider, wobbles away off the seam to Paine
shorter in length, cuts back and draws the edge as Gayle pushes down the wrong line, looking to midwicket, and the ball flies off the face wide of gully
fuller and angling away, Dowlin shoulders arms
pulls back the length but still can't make Dowlin play
third ball in a row pitches and angles past Dowlin who leaves
starts off with a wide, swings away sharply outside leg
stands there and muscles the ball down the track
a bit short in length and Gayle pounces with a punch past the covers
that is off the middle, as Gayle cashes in on the room and smacks the ball past extra cover
oof! Again Harris bowls short and again Gayle puts him past cover
down the pads and he tucks it away toward square leg
fuller ball outside off, heaved with an inside edge past midwicket
gets a short ball and starts to pull but ends up cramped and drags the ball down the track to Bollinger
good length, gets some better lift, and Dowlin hurries to defend
good bounce off the deck again and Dowlin shoulders arms
there's a shot! Dowlin sees room on offer and leans into a nice square drive that threads the gap at backward point
this time the length is spot on and so Dowlin defends
short of a length on the stumps and he defends it back
pitched up on a length and Gayle just bludgeons that past cover
hello! Just a wee bit fuller and same result, Gayle clearing his front foot and smashing that over mid-off
short of a length and it cramps Gayle who pushes it to mid-on
goes back to try and pierce extra cover but ends up picking out mid-off
loud shot from Harris as a shorter ball hits Gayle above the flap as he tries to whip the ball across the stumps
living dangerously, Gayle scoops a shortish ball over cover and it drops wide of two converging fielders
pitched up and Dowlin drives with hard hands to cover, where Hauritz collects and fires to the other end and gives up an overthrow as the sweeper fumbles
short in length, Gayle eases back and steers it to deep point
short of a length on the body and Dowlin tucks it to midwicket, sets off, hesitates, waves Gayle back but his captain is dead keen on the sharp single
and that's why, because he's dealing in boundaries! Stunning pull shot over square leg, connected with all the timing and power in the world
gets up on one leg and puts the short ball into the gap at midwicket
again back goes the leg, again the room is created, and again Gayle connects well, this time swatting the ball safely over mid-on's head
pitches just short of a length and cuts back in sharply to rap Dowlin above the flap, he's on the hop and the bat comes down late but he did get outside the line
shuffles and turns this one to square leg
slants back in and he uses the wrists to tuck the ball past square leg, running very hard and Gayle supports him too
good length, some more cut, and Dowlin stabs it to the on side
nicked and taken! This time Harris pitches the ball just outside off and gets some good bounce off the deck, forcing Dowlin to nibble at it and Paine does the rest
pushes his first ball watchfully to the leg side
backs away and drives the length ball down to mid-off

super ball and now Gayle edges to Paine! His woes against Bollinger continue as he's sucked into feeling for a gem of a ball that pitches middle and off and deviates, taking the outer edge high off the bat
short ball to try and unsettle him, he gets up and works it to midwicket
big shot to a fuller one but he cannot connect, that was close
beaten again with that probing line, forced to feel for it
straighter one and Deonarine gets off the mark with a tap to mid-on
short of a length, gets bat on ball and defends it to cover
again on the dime and Deonarine defends to cover
drives across the line and chips the ball over midwicket's head, Hopes gives chase and slides near the ropes to save four
works across the line to midwicket
walks across the stumps and has to defend as the length is short
ah, beaten! Now its Simmons' turn to feel for a lifter outside off
another good ball sits up and takes the shoulder of the bat as Deonarine is sucked into playing, but the edge evades the slips and gully
hits a length and Simmons keeps bat and pad together
hits another good spot and Simmons has to check the on-drive
a bit shorter and slanting across Simmons who cuts and misses
gets back to cover off and defends the shorter ball to cover
shapes away from middle and off and Simmons shoulders arms
pitches outside off and Deonarine leaves it be
big ugly heave to one pitching closer to the stumps and he misses
holds back the length and gets Deonarine defending
now he connects and slaps a short ball over covers for four
pitches middle and straightens, Deonarine clips out to Harris who does well in the deep
gets forward and pushes the ball to extra cover, calling early
and he strikes first ball! Not a wicket-taking ball, short and there to be hit, but Simmons succeeds in pulling and picking out the one man out in the deep
good ball to get first up, seaming away from the bat
pushes off the front foot this time and is beaten again
stabs at this one pitching on about leg stump
has a good look at this one, covers off, and leaves it be
ooooh! Fuller, straighter, and somehow missing the bat as Hinds, without footwork, drives and misses
starts off short to Deonarine who shuffles and knocks it off the pads
short of a length outside off and Hinds tucks the bat inside the line
bouncer to unsettle him and Hinds takes his eyes off it as he tries to weave out of harm's way
fuller in length and Hinds meets it with a straight bat
throws the bat at width and slashes an edge down to third man, first runs for Hinds since October 2006, the opposition was Australia, the venue was Bombay
hops back into position and keeps out a short ball
channels past at a good height and he pulls out of it
this time he's forced to play and is beaten by the angle and carry
pitches outside off, shapes back in, but he leaves with a stride in
tucked off the pads out to the deep
gets bat and pad together and pushes the ball to cover
short of a length, gets back and runs it off the edge to gully
this time he covers off and defends nicely
again short, this time he hops up and forces it to cover
in the corridor outside off, good lift, no shot offered
short and wide and Deonarine throws the bat at it, slashing over gully
short again but down the leg side, he tries to pull but misses
slashes again, just between cover and point this time in the air
short of a length on the stumps and Hinds defends
angles across off and he watches it go
good cut off the deck, going away from Hinds who lets it
pitches and straightens and he works the ball past midwicket
lands outside leg and moves in, Deonarine is late on the flick
gets back and pushes it to cover
good length outside off and he taps it to the off side
slapped away really hard to the off side but short cover does well to stop it
gives him width outside off and he angles it down to third man
fullish in length outside off and he drives him wide of mid-off
pulls too early and the ball brushes the pads before reaching the keeper, stifled appeal and umpire Reiffel reckons that hit the pad
angles across the left-hander and he safely shoulders arms
good length on middle and leg and he clips it straight to midwicket
great timing, angles across the left-hander and Hinds gets beside the line and slices him wide of backward point, didn't try to hit it too hard
gets forward and pushes it to the off side
tucks it to the deep on the on side
a shot for the album, the ball is pitched up on middle and leg and he offers the full face of the bat and elegantly scoops him over long-on, lovely follow through
stays back and punches it to mid-off
turns and skids, good decision to leave it
skids through, hits his pads and rolls down the pitch
goes back and defends to the off side
waits for the turn and punches it to point
gets forward and defends
stays beside the line and steers him to sweeper cover
full and straight and he pushes it through the line towards mid-on
drops it short of a length, he rocks back and pulls to deep square leg
stand and deliver, the ball is fuller on middle and leg and he gets his high backlift down and clubs it wide of mid-on, doesn't bother to run
on the pads and he tucks it to fine leg
short and wide and he slashes it in the air down to Johnson at third man
slower through the air, he gets well forward and steers it to cover
chips down the track and he checks his shot
flighted on middle  and leg and he tucks it to midwicket
the extra flight encourages him to go over the top and he connects well with that slog sweep, places it to deep midwicket
lunges forward and defends it
tossed up outside off and he gets forward and steers him to cover
slow through the air, he gets forward and defends
stays back and decides to defend
gets forward and defends to the off side
gets forward and pushes it down the pitch
down the leg side and he's nearly stumped off the wide
well played, he opens the face of the bat late and dabs it down to short third man
